modules.description: Provides functions for initializing audio devices, reading and writing audio data, and managing audio streams. Works with raw audio buffers, sample rates, and channel configurations. Used to implement cross-platform audio playback and recording in applications requiring low-level control.

The module offers low-level audio processing capabilities, including stream management, device configuration, and buffer manipulation via callbacks and sample format settings. It works with audio devices, stream objects, and buffer structures, enabling precise control over input/output operations. Use cases include real-time audio processing, streaming applications, and handling complex audio workflows with customizable buffer sizes and sample rates.
